The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Atapattu back, but Mahela stays captain

Colombo: A fit-again Maravan Atapattu has returned to the Sri Lankan squad for the tri-series against India and South Africa later this month but Mahela Jayawardene would continue to lead the side after impressive performances on the England tour and the first Test against the Proteas. 

Atapattu, who was out of the team for five months due to an acute disc problem in his lower back, which required surgery, was named in a 15-man squad for the tournament which gets under way on August 14. Kumar Sangakkara will stay as vice-captain, a SLC release said. 

Tri-Series SQUAD 

Mahela Jayawardene (captain), Maravan Atapattu, Kumar Sangakkara, Muttiah Muralidharan, Sanath Jayasuriya, Upul Tharanga, Tillekeratne Dilshan, Chamara Kapugedera, Farveez Mahroof, Chaminda Vaas, Lasith Malinga, Dilhara Fernando, Malinga Bandara, Ruchira Perera, Prasanna Jayawardene. Coach: Tom Moody. 

 (PTI) 




